# Part 2 — Describe a person who makes plans a lot

One person who immediately comes to mind is one of my close friends from university. His name is Kevin, and we’ve known each other for about three years because we study in the same major, which is computer science. What really stands out about him is that he’s extremely organized and always planning ahead, sometimes months in advance.

For example, he makes detailed study plans before every semester starts. He divides his goals into weekly tasks and even tracks his progress using apps like Notion. Besides academic planning, he also plans his future career very carefully. He’s already preparing for internships, improving his coding skills, and researching graduate schools abroad, even though graduation is still quite far away. Sometimes he also creates travel plans for our friend group, including transportation, accommodation, budgets, and backup options in case something unexpected happens.

I think I know him so well because we often work together on programming projects and participate in competitions together. During those experiences, I noticed that he rarely does things impulsively. Instead, he prefers to think several steps ahead, which makes him very reliable. If there’s a deadline approaching, he’s usually the calmest person in the group because everything has already been arranged in advance.

Personally, I really admire this quality. In my opinion, planning can reduce stress and improve efficiency, especially for students. At the same time, I think it’s important not to become overly rigid. Sometimes life is unpredictable, so people should leave some room for flexibility as well. Overall, though, I believe he’s someone worth learning from because his self-discipline and long-term thinking are genuinely impressive.

---

### 中文翻译：

我第一时间想到的人是我大学里的一位好朋友。他叫 Kevin，我们认识大概三年了，因为我们是同一个专业的，也就是计算机科学。他最突出的特点就是特别有规划性，而且总是提前做计划，有时候甚至提前好几个月。

比如说，每学期开学前，他都会制定详细的学习计划。他会把目标拆分成每周任务，还会用 Notion 之类的软件记录进度。除了学习之外，他对未来职业的规划也非常认真。他已经开始准备实习、提升编程能力、研究国外研究生项目，尽管离毕业还有一段时间。有时候他还会给我们朋友一起出行做计划，包括交通、住宿、预算，甚至连突发情况的备选方案都考虑好了。

我之所以这么了解他，是因为我们经常一起做编程项目，也会一起参加比赛。在这些经历中，我发现他很少冲动做事，而是习惯提前思考好几步，所以他特别可靠。如果快到截止日期了，他通常是团队里最冷静的人，因为他早就安排好了所有事情。

我个人非常欣赏这种品质。我觉得提前规划能减少压力、提高效率，尤其对于学生来说更重要。当然，我也认为人不能太死板，因为生活总会有一些不可预测的事情，所以还是要保留一定的灵活性。总体来说，我觉得他是一个非常值得学习的人，因为他的自律和长远思维真的令人佩服。

